&gt;Any advice? Do I have the right to tell the insurance party that they
&gt;must fix my car with new parts?

"/> Contact your own insurance company for help. (You should have
reported the accident to them anyway, regardless of fault.)

In general(*) you are entitled to the money it will take to restore
the car to the shape it was in before the collision. If that can be
done with used parts, that's legal and appropriate. But the used
parts must not be of lower quality than the parts you had before the
collision.

(*) The exception is when it would cost more than the car was worth
before the accident; when the car is &quot;totaled&quot; in insurance lingo.
But it doesn't sound like that's the case here.

--
