R&gt; Any advice? Do I have the right to tell the insurance party that they
R&gt; must fix my car with new parts?

besides what others said, remember, you don't have even to deal with other party's
insurance co. The damage to your car was caused by the driver, your claim for damages
is to him, and the fact that he has an insurance policy is relevant for him, not for
you. You don't have any direct business with his insurance, and they don't have any
obligations to you.

Technically, you can repair your car as you see fit, and then claim the costs from
another driver, possibly with a lawsuit. On practice, you adjust for his insurance
policies in order to increase the chances of getting the money.

