Mine, for example, specifies that my rate will be increased for an
accident that does not fit into one of several categories. One of the
categories is that my insurance company recovers at least 60% of the
claim; this is the company's definition of &quot;not at fault&quot;, which is not
identical to the legal definition. (Other categories include clear
not-at-fault situations, such as damage to your car when it is legally
parked, or when it is hit in the rear unless you were given a moving
violation.)

